    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n4804" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἶρις</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝῖρις</span>), dat. pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἴ̄ρισσιν</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">rainbow</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 11.27</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
          17.547</span></i>.—Personified, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ἶρις,
          ιδος</span>, acc. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ἶριν</span>, voc.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ἶρι</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">Iris</span>, messenger
          of the gods in the Iliad. To men she usually appears under the assumed
          form of some mortal.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
